The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                Sanchita Dey, 25, died after being allegedly hit with a brick by Anjana Nandi, 38. Anjana, who was separated from her husband Saswata for six months, went to his house at Sashtri Narendranath Ganguli Road in Howrah on Tuesday night and found Sanchita in the bedroom. Anjana allegedly attacked her with a brick. Sanchita was admitted to Howrah District Hospital in critical condition. Saswata and Anjana were arrested.     Civic authorities on Wednesday demolished a part of an illegal construction at 5 Ripon Lane in central Calcutta. The illegal construction was allegedly carried out by Idris Ali, the president of All India Minority Forum. The civic squad abandoned the demolition mid-way on the request of former Congress leader Somen Mitra. Ali has promised to demolish the illegally constructed part himself, said an official.    Manisha Das, a Class VI student of Jogendranath Adarsa High School in Barasat, lodged a police complaint against her mathematics teacher Aloka Shome on Wednesday for beating her without proper reason. Manishas mother said her daughter had to be taken to Barasat District Hospital with hearing problems after the alleged beating.    A fight broke out between members of SFI and DSO at the Institute of Post Graduate Medical Education amp; Research on Wednesday morning. Officials said the union members were trying to enlist supporters.    Daily passengers on Barasat-Bongaon route blocked railway tracks at Ashokenagar station for over two hours on Wednesday morning. They demanded punishment for members of the CITU-affiliated railway hawkers unit who allegedly beat up passengers last week. Police cleared the tracks.    Prasanta Sikari, 26, the cleaner of a milk van, died after the vehicle hit a truck on Mahendra Bhattacharya Road in Howrah, on Tuesday morning.                                                                                                                                                              
